<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 28 at 3:49AM EDT  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...ELEVATED FIRE WEATHER CONCERNS TODAY AND FRIDAY FOR
WESTERN MASSACHUSETTS...
A very dry airmass will combine with gusty northwest winds,
resulting in elevated fire weather concerns today and Friday.
Northwest winds 15 to 20 mph with gusts of 30 to 35 mph are
expected today, and around 10 to 15 mph with gusts up to 30 mph
for Friday. Minimum relative humidities between 20 to 25 percent
are expected both days.</description>
